                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 New Delhi, Nov. 19: The cabinet today approved an increase in its per-child allocations under the mid-day meal scheme.           
	From a uniform per-child allocation of Rs 2 a day, the new norms stipulate that Rs 2.5 will be spent per day on each primary school child and Rs 3.75 for upper primary  Classes VI to VIII  children. Upper primary children will receive 30 grams of pulsses a day under the new norms. Cooks will receive for the first time an honorarrium of Rs 1,000 a month.                   
	 Chenna (PTI): Madras High Court has directed the Tamil Nadu government to pay a compensation of Rs 8 lakh to a woman who had been raped by a police inspector 25 years ago. The court described the victim, now 53 years old, as a role model for women for carrying on her fight for so long. In these 25 years, the inspector got promoted to the rank of deputy superintendent.                   
	Lucknow (PTI): A newborn tiger cub died at Lucknow zoo on Wednesday. The cub, which was in the ICU at the zoo because it was very weak, is the third cub of Bengal tigress Ipshita to have died this week.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): A Delhi court on Thursday granted bail to a man accused of blackmailing sitarist Anoushka Shankar with her private photographs. The court said it was not useful to keep Junaid Khan in jail as he has been in custody since September 14.
                                                                                                                                              
